{[show S]

The bidding has gone as shown. It is your bid. [BID 3\S]



You have an opening hand with four of partner's Major suit so naturally you want to force to game. Although you could bid a Jacoby 2NT, the presence of the singleton \S makes a Splinter Bid more attractive. So you double-jump to 3\S. Partner now bids 4\C. What do you say next? [BID 4\D]

[show NS]



Partner's 4\C bid is control showing, and indicates he is thinking slammish. You bid 4\D showing your control and partner bids 6\H.

As you can see, North should make 12 tricks by discarding one \C loser on your \DA.}


